- cs.CG (Computational Geometry) is the most likely category as the paper is focused on improving algorithms for two fundamental problems in computational geometry. 
- cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) is also likely as the paper proposes a new algorithm for solving a class of regularized saddle-point problems. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is another possible category as the paper discusses improvements in running time for iterative algorithms. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics) is a possible category as the paper deals with optimization problems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper proposes a novel saddle-point optimization framework.
